{"TopicId":179131,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Great Shift - The Gram to Be Redefined","CreatedByName":"XB-70A","CreatedById":144985,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T12:56:44Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"XB-70A","CreatedById":144985,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T12:56:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat news!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn 2018-11-13/16, the I.S.U. will redefine the gram (and also the A and the K) by switching from its actual material base,\u00A0the famous \u003Cem\u003EInternational Prototype Kilogram\u003C/em\u003E, but whose mass has slowly varied along the years, to an \u003Cstrong\u003Eimmaterial\u003C/strong\u003E one related to the Planck constant (J*s)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore available on this page:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://news.cnrs.fr/articles/measures-the-great-shift\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://news.cnrs.fr/articles/measures-the-great-shift\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022data_new_kg_72dpi.png?itok=UxxvfzUe\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022475\u0022 src=\u0022https://news.cnrs.fr/sites/default/files/styles/asset_image_full/public/assets/images/data_new_kg_72dpi.png?itok=UxxvfzUe\u0022 width=\u0022664\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T13:56:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow. That was about time. I knew that the prototypes had problems holding their \u003Cs\u003Eweight\u003C/s\u003E mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlad to read that a kg is still a kg \u003Cspan\u003E:-)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Racescort666","CreatedById":137852,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T14:00:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRelevant Veritasium video (also very interesting if you\u2019ve got 10 minutes to watch):\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Oo0jm1PPRuo?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T16:36:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223471838\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179131\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540040204\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144985\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022XB-70A\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, XB-70A said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Gram to Be Redefined\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*Kilogram\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m glad they finally went somewhere with both the kibble balance and the spherical silicone monocrystal atom measurement.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally the title of this video can be put to rest.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/JKCBeDeVxkg?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-20T16:41:52Z\u0022 title=\u002210/20/2018 04:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 20, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T16:46:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223471966\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179131\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540053400\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*Kilogram\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m glad they finally went somewhere with both the kibble balance and the spherical silicone monocrystal atom measurement.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally the title of this video can be put to rest.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like Avagadro\u0027s number will require measurement of that sphere and comparison to the Planck constant and not the other way around.\u00A0 Makes sense, the Planck constant is certainly seen as more fundamental, but I always liked the Avagdro number.\u00A0 In other news, we should be adding a few decimal places to Avagardo\u0027s number, even if it won\u0027t be exact.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T16:49:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo can I trade in all my old kilograms for the new ones, or are they just junk?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T16:55:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo no, keep them ! They automagically adopt the new flavour. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t be fooled by somebody telling you \u0022Hey, pssst, I can trade all your old kg into new ones. Special price.\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-20T16:59:39Z\u0022 title=\u002210/20/2018 04:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 20, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DerekL1963","CreatedById":57091,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T17:44:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223471974\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179131\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540054149\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150244\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nightside\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n50 minutes ago, Nightside said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo can I trade in all my old kilograms for the new ones, or are they just junk?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nUnless you\u0027re doing lab or reference standard grade measurement, you can keep and continue to use your old kilograms.\u00A0 If you are doing precision measurement using laboratory or reference grade kilograms, then your metrology people will have some thinking to do on how to handle the changeover.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nOr, to put it more simply, unless you\u0027re currently using a managed standard, you probably won\u0027t have to do anything.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lajoswinkler","CreatedById":79159,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T18:00:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223471977\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179131\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540054548\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t be fooled by somebody telling you \u0022Hey, pssst, I can trade all your old kg into new ones. Special price.\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGod damn it. Thwarted again!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"satnet","CreatedById":147366,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T22:47:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would also like to add Practical Engineering\u0027s video. It doesn\u0027t go quite as deep into the subject as Veritasium, but he actually builds one himself. This is why I always preferred the Kibble balance approach. Basically it can be replicated by anyone with reasonable effort (though for extreme precision/accuracy you still need the resources of a nation-state or at least a large corporation).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/ewQkE8t0xgQ?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T23:50:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally. What a stupid way to define something so critical.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-20T23:50:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223471972\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179131\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540053998\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133850\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wumpus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, wumpus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAvagadro\u0027s\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Enumber will require measurement of that sphere and comparison to the Planck constant and not the other way\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Earound\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom what I\u0027ve heard from Derek Muller (Veritasium) they\u0027ll compare their results. I think the kibble balance is ultimately chosen because of the ease of actually doing it in other places (so rather than needing national kilogram copies they can just calibrate their environment and build their own balance, much like atomic clocks), but they had to crosscheck with the result from the atom lattice measurement. As the two results agree strongly, the whole replacement is given the go-ahead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean, if they had locked the Planck\u0027s Constant and the value for speed of light, it\u0027s not too surprising that Avogadro\u0027s number will also be locked down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s his video with the silicone crystal sphere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZMByI4s-D-Y?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-20T23:53:19Z\u0022 title=\u002210/20/2018 11:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 20, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-21T00:06:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts a bit fun, one meter was defined by the distance from pole to equator. Yes it was selected as the length was decent for everyday use. it was also inaccurate \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo they made an standard bar, that is also easier to replicate.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nLater they defined it on light eliminating the need for an unique bar.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nOne liter is 0.1 meter\u00A0 cubed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne Kg is one liter of water, that is at 4 centigrade an also has inaccuracies so they made an new unique weight, its now replaced by physical constants.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}